Reasoning: The paper proposes a methodology for visualizing and analyzing time-spatial data using artificial neural net techniques. This involves a back-end data model, clustering method, and prediction approach, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of graphics, animation, and 3D models for visualization, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and interactive systems (cs.SI). Lastly, the paper discusses abnormal traffic pattern detection, which could fall under computer security (cs.CR).
